From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: add disk-name = "SD" property to sdmmc-disk node

Empirically, the only build that successfully completed SD init had
this property in the DTS. Without it, CMD0 times out -116 even at
1 MHz. Possibly Zephyr's sdmmc_subsys.c needs the property even
though docs say it's ignored.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay b/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
@@ -12,6 +12,7 @@
         mmc {
             compatible = "zephyr,sdmmc-disk";
             status = "okay";
+            disk-name = "SD";
         };
         spi-max-frequency = <1000000>;  // patch 0017: 1 MHz for breadboard wiring
     };
